   <ab type="translation"
       xml:id="p0364_translation"
       corresp="#p0364_transcription">
         "and let thy heart take courage, and wait thou for the Lord. 
         I believe to see the good things 
         of the Lord in the land of the living."
         <!-- DRB Psalm 26 Verse 14 -->
         "The just shall be had in everlasting remembrance. 
         They shall not fear for the evil tidings. 
         Our father [in secret]. And [lead us] not into temptation."
         <!-- OBDS pg 420 -->
         Answer me. How many 
         are my iniquities and sins? 
         make me know my crimes and offences
         Why hidest thou thy face, 
         and thinkest me thy enemy? Against a leaf, 
         that is carried away with the wind, thou shewest thy power, 
         and thou pursuest a dry straw. 
         For thou writest bitter things against me," <!-- DRBO Book of Job 13:23-13:26 -->
         
         
